subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
This species resembles 

P. manueli

in the shape of the palpal bulb and the patterns of sternum and carapace, but can be distinguished from it by the broad axe-shaped appendix (
Fig. 56H
), by the shape of the tip of the procursus (
Figs. 56G–I
), and by the relatively small pore plates of the epigynum (
Fig. 56B
).
